OL,3,CCraig Bellamy announced as new Wales
OL,4,Cmanager to replace Rob Page
OL,6,FSince Rob Page's departure the FAW had
OL,7,Fsuggested they were ready to appoint
OL,8,Ftheir first non-Welsh manager for 25
OL,9,Fyears but opting for Bellamy over
OL,10,Fcandidates like Thierry Henry and
OL,11,FWilly Sagnol has obvious benefits.
OL,13,FBellamy, who played for his country 78
OL,14,Ftimes will need no introduction to the
OL,15,Fculture that the Welsh national side
OL,16,Fhas fostered over the last decade or
OL,17,Fso.
