OL,3,CCraig Bellamy announced as new Wales
OL,4,Cmanager to replace Rob Page
OL,6,FWhatever Bellamy's tenure brings, it's
OL,7,Funlikely to be boring.
OL,9,FBellamy has spent the last two seasons
OL,10,Fat Burnley, where he worked as number
OL,11,Ftwo to Vincent Kompany. He was then
OL,12,Fput in interim charge of the club when
OL,13,FKompnay left for Bayern Munich in May
OL,14,Fbut is now set to return to home soil
OL,15,Fin Wales
OL,17,FThe former Wales player began his
OL,18,Fcoaching career in the academy of
OL,19,Fhometown club Cardiff.
